Class
Description
AbstractQuery
Abstract class, parent for CQuery and DQuery
Holds variables every query should have.
AnalyticalTool
 
AnalyticalToolForFiles
Interface to work with files using the tool

Interface to work with streams using the tool
App
Main class to use the Analytical Tool.
Category
Represents a Service
service_id[.variation_id]
And/or Question
question_type_id[.category_id.[sub-category_id]
CategoryProvider
Represents Factory for Categories
Takes a String value and parses it
CQuery
C queries

Examples:
C 1 1 P 01.01.2022 10
C 2 2 P 02.02.2012 20
C 3 3.1 P 03.03.2022 30

Format:
C/D service_id[.sub_service_id] question_id[.sub_question_id[.sub_question_id]] P/N dd.mm.yyyy minutes
values in square brackets are optional
DQuery
D Queries

Examples:
D 1 1 P 01.01.2022-02.01.2022
D 2 2 P 01.02.2022-03.02.2022
D 3 3.1 P 01.03.2022-04.03.2022

Format:
C/D service_id[.sub_service_id] question_id[.sub_question_id[.sub_question_id]] P/N dd.mm.yyyy dd.mm.yyyy
values in square brackets are optional
service_id[.sub_service_id] might be * (only whole value, sub_service_id can't be *)
question_id[.sub_question_id[.sub_question_id]] the same
first dd.mm.yyyy represents the starting day to monitor, later represents the last one.
QueryProvider
Represents a Factory providing Queries based on input
Variants are
from(String list) (for testing), from(Stream lines) - get multiple queries
fromLine(String line) - get single query
